    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-09-14T11:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-09-14T11:45:00-05:00" n="489"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.51/1999: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-09-14T11:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>343. Department’s 177, September 11, 2 [<hi rend="italic">5?</hi>] p.m., last
                    paragraph. President Diaz has readily given the desired assurances.</p>
                <p>We still feel that it would be desirable to have the greater part of the proceeds
                    of the dividend withheld until after the election. President Diaz desired this
                    to protect himself from pressure to make it available for political or other
                    irregular purposes. Otherwise it would be difficult for President Diaz to resist
                    such pressure and it would be entirely impossible for the Legation to ascertain
                    how the money was in fact being used.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
